article.description: USD wins its 4th straight vs. N. Kentucky, 75-44
article.headline: USD wins its 4th straight vs. N. Kentucky, 75-44
article.linkText: USD wins its 4th straight vs. N. Kentucky, 75-44
article.story: HIGHLAND HEIGHTS, Ky. -- Dennis Kramer scored 15 points and Jito Kok grabbed 12 rebounds to lead San Diego to its fourth straight victory this season in a 75-44 win over Northern Kentucky on Saturday night. Kramer shot 6 of 7 from the field as the Toreros (4-0) finished 26 of 50 (52 percent) from the floor. A 4-0 record hasn't happened at USD since the 1990-91 season. The Torero's held an 11-point lead at halftime and outscored Northern Kentucky by 20 points in the second half. Daniel Camps came off the bench for the Norse and was the only teammate to score in double digits with 11 points. Northern Kentucky (0-3) attempted 28 3-pointers but made just 3 (10.7 percent). The Norse had 21 offensive rebounds, compared to 8 for San Diego, but only made 11 points on second-chance shots. The Toreros grabbed 36 defensive rebounds and Northern Kentucky had 19.
